20/04/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader said on Saturday (April 19th) that Croatia has never been in a better international position. Marking the 100th day of his government, he cited the country's recent invitation to join NATO and the visit of US President George W. Bush. At the same time, Sanader acknowledged that Croatia, like other countries around the world, is struggling with soaring oil and food prices. Sanader was speaking to the Croatian Peasants' Party, a coalition partner of his Croatian Democratic Union. (Poslovni Dnevnik, HRT, Javno.com, Vecernji List - 19/04/08)
